author: Chris Oberholtz, Multimedia Producer
title: Three hurt in KCK crash
text:
KANSAS CITY, KS (KCTV) - Three people are were hurt after a single-vehicle crash early Sunday morning.
The wreck happened about 12:30 a.m. in the 900 block of Central Avenue
Police said a black Mercury Sable was heading east on Central Avenue when it left the roadway and struck a tree. The three victims were taken to area hospitals. Two people were in critical condition.
The accident remains under investigation.
